---
title: Thai Chili Coconut Smashed Pork Patties with Zesty Rice, Roasted Green Beans & Peanuts
description: If you take a meatball and smash it flat before cooking, a little kitchen magic happens: All those jagged, craggy edges that form get extra crisp and caramelized when roasting in the oven. Coat those patties with a sweet and spicy Thai chili coconut pan sauce and serve over zesty rice along with tender green beans. Finish with a scattering of roasted peanuts and squeezes of lime, and you’ve taken the humble meatball into fiercely delicious territory!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/thai-chili-coconut-smashed-pork-patties-f5a368f5.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/646bdeb0b4f5a4b633f5c63b.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/thai-chili-coconut-smashed-pork-patties-646bdeb0b4f5a4b633f5c63b
time required: 40 minutes
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 910 kcal
  fat: 54 g
  saturated fat: 27 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 760 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

Thoroughly shake @coconut milk{1%unit} in container before opening.

In a #small pot{}, combine ¼ cup coconut milk (you'll use the rest later), ½ cup @water{1/2%cup}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. (For 4 servings, use ½ cup coconut milk, 1 cup water, 2 TBSP butter, and 1 tsp sugar.)

Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}; cover, and reduce heat to low. Cook until liquid has absorbed and rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, ginger, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}.

Form into 10-12 1 1/2-inch meatballs.

> For 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp salt.

Place meatballs on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Using a lightly oiled #spatula{}, smash meatballs to make ¾-inch-thick patties. Toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast patties on middle rack and green beans on top rack.)

Roast on top rack until patties are cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

When patties and green beans have 5 minutes left, combine @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} with remaining coconut milk in a #large pan{}; heat over medium-high heat. Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced by about half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and season with salt and pepper.

Add patties to pan with coconut chili sauce; toss to coat.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with patties and green beans. Spoon any remaining sauce over patties. Sprinkle with @peanuts{1/2%ounce}(roasted). Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.